Quote:  The last I shal [sic] mention is the Fan-Tail. Of these there are different sorts, but the body of the most remarkable one is scarce larger than a good Filbert, yet spreads a tail of most beautiful plumage full 3/4 of a semi-circle, of, at least, 4 or 5 Inches radius.
Notes:  1773 Wales Journal in 1961 Cook's Journals 2/786

